putting my kitty to sleep help '' kitty is years old and he isnt doing so good and im ive had him by my side all my life and i cry over the idea of him not being by my bed in the morning anymore but i dont want him suffering but then yet again i dont know how bad ill take it it would be like losing a brother please any help about anything would be appreciated sweetheart which is worse your pain or his yes it is terribly painful to loose a pet they are like our babies but you do not want him to suffer if the vet says there is nothing to do then go ahead and do the right thing by your best buddy they feel no pain with the euthanasia they give them a large dose of morphine and they simply go to sleep talk to him tell him how much you love him and will miss him in the wild he would have simply have gone off alone to die do this for him if the vet says there is no hope in time you will learn to love another kitten and your healing will begin i know how badly this hurts i have had to put down my family dog myself and it was like killing my best friend to me even though she was in such pain and couldn't walk or pee or even move i knew it was the right thing we were in a blizzard and there was no hope for her to survive through it i have had others put down as well by the vet and it is never an easy thing to do think about getting another kitten in a few months when you are ready their joy and playfulness will help heal you good luck and kiss your darling friend for me Garfield Shaggy dog story EastEnders Atomic Kitten Humphrey Bogart Jon Secada Days of our Lives Guinea pig One Tree Hill (TV series) Ferret Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Friends Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Avenue Q AFI 100 Years series Sin City Cliff Richard 1957 World Series Pitaten Kodocha Babe Ruth RuneScape quests Euthanasia Main characters of Fullmetal Alchemist Happiness Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Simone Weil Characters in the Smurfs Theory of conduct Freddy Fender Badly Drawn Kitties